 {"id":"bd-1e2","title":"Create integration test suite for component interoperability","description":"## Purpose and Rationale

Create integration tests that verify components work correctly together. While unit tests verify individual components and E2E tests verify the whole system, integration tests focus on component boundaries and interactions.

## Background

Integration bugs often occur at boundaries between components:
- Console + Theme interaction
- Renderer + Console interaction  
- DisplayContext affecting multiple components
- Config affecting all subsystems

## Test Scenarios

### 1. Theme-Console Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_theme_styles_applied_by_console() {
    let theme = FastMcpTheme::builder()
        .primary_color("#00ff00")
        .build()
        .unwrap();

    let tc = TestConsole::new_with_theme(theme.clone());
    tc.console().print("[primary]Test[/]");

    // Verify the custom color was applied
    let raw = tc.raw_output().join("");
    // Check for the ANSI code corresponding to #00ff00
}
```

### 2. Renderer-Console Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_error_renderer_uses_console_correctly() {
    let tc = TestConsole::new_rich();
    let renderer = RichErrorRenderer::new(
        tc.console().theme().clone(),
        tc.console().context().clone(),
    );

    let error = Error::Internal("test".into());
    renderer.render(&error, tc.console());

    // Verify output went to the right place
    assert!(!tc.output().is_empty());
}

#[test]
fn test_multiple_renderers_share_console() {
    let tc = TestConsole::new_rich();

    // Use multiple renderers with same console
    let error_renderer = RichErrorRenderer::new(/* ... */);
    let stats_renderer = StatsRenderer::new(/* ... */);
    let tool_renderer = ToolTableRenderer::new(/* ... */);

    error_renderer.render(&Error::Internal("test".into()), tc.console());
    stats_renderer.render_table(&StatsSnapshot::default(), tc.console());
    tool_renderer.render(&[], tc.console());

    // All output should be captured
    tc.assert_contains("error");
    tc.assert_contains("No tools");
}
```

### 3. DisplayContext Propagation

```rust
#[test]
fn test_agent_context_propagates_to_all_renderers() {
    let context = DisplayContext::new_agent();
    let theme = FastMcpTheme::default();

    let renderers = vec![
        RichErrorRenderer::new(theme.clone(), context.clone()),
        StatsRenderer::new(theme.clone(), context.clone()),
        ToolTableRenderer::new(theme.clone(), context.clone()),
    ];

    let tc = TestConsole::new(); // Agent mode

    for renderer in &renderers {
        // Each renderer should respect agent context
        // and not produce ANSI codes
    }

    let raw = tc.raw_output().join("");
    assert!(!raw.contains("\x1b["), "Agent context should suppress all ANSI");
}
```

### 4. Config Propagation

```rust
#[test]
fn test_config_affects_all_components() {
    let config = ConsoleConfig::new()
        .plain_mode()
        .without_banner()
        .without_suggestions();

    let context = config.resolve_context();
    let theme = config.theme.clone();

    // Verify context is agent-like
    assert!(!context.should_use_rich());

    // Verify error renderer respects show_suggestions
    let renderer = RichErrorRenderer::new(theme, context);
    // renderer should not show suggestions
}
```

### 5. Logging Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_rich_logging_integrates_with_console() {
    let tc = TestConsole::new_rich();

    // Initialize logging to capture to test console
    let subscriber = RichSubscriberBuilder::new()
        .with_writer(tc.writer())
        .build();

    tracing::subscriber::with_default(subscriber, || {
        tracing::info!("Test log message");
        tracing::error!("Test error");
    });

    tc.assert_contains("Test log message");
    tc.assert_contains("Test error");
}
```

### 6. Stats Collection Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_stats_collection_integrates_with_renderer() {
    let stats = ServerStats::new();

    // Simulate server activity
    for i in 0..100 {
        let success = i % 10 != 0; // 90% success rate
        stats.record_request("tools/call", Duration::from_millis(10 + i), success);
    }

    let snapshot = stats.snapshot();

    let tc = TestConsole::new();
    let renderer = StatsRenderer::new(/* ... */);
    renderer.render_table(&snapshot, tc.console());

    // Verify stats are accurately reflected
    tc.assert_contains("100"); // Total requests
    tc.assert_contains("90"); // Success count or percentage
}
```

### 7. Handler Registry Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_unified_handler_registry_uses_sub_renderers() {
    let tc = TestConsole::new_rich();

    let tools = vec![/* sample tools */];
    let resources = vec![/* sample resources */];
    let prompts = vec![/* sample prompts */];

    let capabilities = ServerCapabilities { tools, resources, prompts };

    let registry_renderer = HandlerRegistryRenderer::new(/* ... */);
    registry_renderer.render(&capabilities, tc.console());

    // Verify all sections rendered
    tc.assert_contains("Tools");
    tc.assert_contains("Resources");
    tc.assert_contains("Prompts");
}
```

