### Usage Examples

```rust
// Example 1: Full configuration
use fastmcp::Server;
use fastmcp_console::{ConsoleConfig, BannerStyle, TrafficVerbosity};

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    let config = ConsoleConfig::new()
        .with_banner(BannerStyle::Full)
        .with_log_level(tracing::Level::DEBUG)
        .with_traffic(TrafficVerbosity::Summary)
        .with_periodic_stats(30);

    Server::new("my-mcp-server")
        .with_console_config(config)
        .tool(calculate)
        .run_stdio()
        .await
        .unwrap();
}

// Example 2: Builder methods
Server::new("my-mcp-server")
    .with_banner(BannerStyle::Compact)
    .with_traffic_logging(TrafficVerbosity::Headers)
    .plain_mode() // For CI/testing
    .run_stdio()
    .await
    .unwrap();

// Example 3: Environment-driven (production)
Server::new("my-mcp-server")
    // ConsoleConfig::from_env() is default
    .tool(my_tool)
    .run_stdio()
    .await
    .unwrap();
```

### Documentation Updates

Add to README.md:

```markdown
## Console Configuration

FastMCP provides rich console output for debugging and monitoring.

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `FASTMCP_BANNER` | Banner style: full/compact/minimal/none |
| `FASTMCP_LOG` | Log level: trace/debug/info/warn/error |
| `FASTMCP_TRAFFIC` | Traffic logging: none/summary/headers/full |
| `NO_COLOR` | Disable all colors |

### Programmatic Configuration

\`\`\`rust
use fastmcp_console::{ConsoleConfig, BannerStyle};

let server = Server::new("demo")
    .with_console_config(
        ConsoleConfig::new()
            .with_banner(BannerStyle::Compact)
    );
\`\`\`
```

